    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "673212ef2147449292b3ceb89b925f38",
      "x": 26144.020217068824,
      "y": 14052.193032908175,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.775000000000125,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "This is actually significant for your \"rattle.\" The Buddhist sangha framing fits the pacifism beat. Krishna doesn't. So if the unknown quote shares Buddhist substrate on the war question, it's specifically not drawing from the Krishna stream \u2014 even though both are roughly contemporaneous Indic teachings (Gita compiled ~2nd century BCE to 2nd century CE, but the Krishna tradition is older)."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "And add into this context Genesis 3:22",
      "uuid": "9b2e3eb973974f54845eeb20529507f4",
      "x": 1802.8609505050772,
      "y": 2868.3925158189395,
      "width": 405.27610560577136,
      "height": 34.0100134773313,
      "z_value": 10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "And add into this context Genesis 3:22",
      "depth_front": true,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "5f0ab1113e6b40e1a2835b4d0538e2ba",
      "x": 14343.087084456474,
      "y": 7146.123779372387,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.859000000000078,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "I'll diff it against Revelation primarily, with Genesis as a contrast point, and against D&C 45 as the baseline you're working from."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "The Goodness of God",
      "uuid": "9a9ebda6c61a4ccf8996f9da7734bad6",
      "x": 2854.514432560183,
      "y": 1084.6258239138042,
      "width": 284.5317215405141,
      "height": 312.0,
      "z_value": -9.94700000000003,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "We can also add into this the fact that God defines as everything, so of course he is those things as well.\n\nBeing the definition of everything and then just skip emotions and consequences of such...  Then he would be some kind of dictator cherry picking how he likes to be\n\nIn order to be the definition of everything, the universe itself even, he is also these things, so we examine the utilities of each thing that we perceive to be a flaw, and where the extraction and benefit of such is, in general"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "f5d3e0c1e8494f3495aabc17544a9fa8",
      "x": 14742.233402751855,
      "y": 8032.300531857005,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.85600000000008,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The trumpet + waking"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "9dc01fb03a6a4696919fd5722364f4dd",
      "x": 31699.848209125532,
      "y": 20507.678676476848,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.733000000000148,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Now apply this to your unknown quote:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "A spectacle of light",
      "uuid": "600fa5fd200e45cbac4fdf151f523529",
      "x": 29979.750875050708,
      "y": 18051.718233515123,
      "width": 228.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.702000000000165,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "A spectacle of light",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "2fe4ba5791214620980b8cb65eb89a39",
      "x": 14535.723771328336,
      "y": 7403.355176229043,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.858000000000079,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The light + parable as sign"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "b7aff8f951824f92b30d12c7c709540f",
      "x": 22135.386466538326,
      "y": 12309.869689903693,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.814000000000103,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "That's a genuinely different category of \"rattle.\" It's the difference between \"this echoes scripture\" and \"scripture echoes this.\""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "fb1049bd1ec845b89c3c15fe5bb85d7a",
      "x": 22195.19999193504,
      "y": 13458.815823422503,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.807000000000107,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "I won't press for the source. But the shape of what you're describing \u2014 older than the Abrahamic apocalyptic tradition, containing a coherent five-beat eschatology including a pacifism marker, with a first-person-plural awakened voice \u2014 narrows the field considerably. There aren't many traditions that fit all of that. If you ever want to think out loud about it without naming it directly, I'm happy to keep triangulating."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Matthew 16:18",
      "uuid": "859e9ec5c8c34e348bebcac8d11206f1",
      "x": 5117.036914374417,
      "y": 2196.4143703397294,
      "width": 308.52635703653254,
      "height": 123.26278667120636,
      "z_value": -9.901000000000055,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "I tell you that you are Peter, and it is on this rock that I will build my congregation, and the powers of hell will not conquer it"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "b61047fba3f34ce897feb39bd4431a73",
      "x": 15093.768757851005,
      "y": 10695.026495250959,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.847000000000085,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Genesis is the strongest contrast. Genesis is full of patriarchal warfare \u2014 Abraham raising 318 men to rescue Lot (Genesis 14), Jacob's sons sacking Shechem (Genesis 34), Jacob blessing Judah as a \"lion's whelp\" (Genesis 49). The covenant in Genesis is explicitly not gated on non-violence; it's gated on faith and obedience. Genesis 22:18's \"all nations blessed\" is because Abraham obeyed in a moment that is itself violent (the binding of Isaac)."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "46cc8e7b152542519ed160ae5f55dcd7",
      "x": 14680.17517232629,
      "y": 7130.113937371838,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.861000000000077,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Searched the web\nSearched the web\nNow I have what I need. Let me work through this comparison carefully."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "449de7444a3f411ab09116dabc8640c5",
      "x": 23995.788782241038,
      "y": 14094.190128288572,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.798000000000112,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "\"I will ensure you can translate all of this\" \u2014 this is the awkward one for a Buddhist reading. The Buddhist transmission concern is real (the Tripitaka's movement from Pali to Sanskrit to Chinese to Tibetan involved enormous translation effort), but the promise of translatability isn't a characteristic Buddhist statement. The Buddha's framing is more often \"the dharma is the dharma regardless of language\" \u2014 translation is assumed possible, not promised. Though some Mahayana sutras do have the Buddha promising the teaching will reach distant lands and times, which is functionally adjacent."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Note",
      "uuid": "1d1ae715de76421b94755cb141b9132a",
      "x": 4276.121947738935,
      "y": 1456.338307138427,
      "width": 115.06123786589023,
      "height": 29.0205218600654,
      "z_value": -9.943000000000032,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Beautiful",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#2a3a2f"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "So that we can confirm that his plan indeed did work great",
      "uuid": "be4d587d1dae4d4786d6c864a1d1d3b8",
      "x": 1598.1291005723433,
      "y": 2792.875471105439,
      "width": 604.878481559447,
      "height": 32.885266566655105,
      "z_value": 10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "So that we can confirm that his plan indeed did work great",
      "depth_front": true,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Accurate",
      "uuid": "0c0909aa17944626856fa4db27ec73c0",
      "x": 6745.169773344722,
      "y": 3101.2625581757056,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 1992.0,
      "z_value": -9.902000000000054,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Let me write the benchmark first so we have a baseline, then add the gate, then re-run.\n\n\nCreated a file, ran 2 commands, edited a file\nBaseline captured. 50 nodes animating simultaneously costs ~41ms/sec of CPU (~4% of one core), 100 nodes hits ~74ms/sec (~7.4%). That's the \"vibrance tax\" we're paying at street level \u2014 fine. Now adding the aerial gate.\n\nEdited\nNodeBehaviour.py\n+10\n-1\nNow add _should_pulse() and gate the three entry points.\n\n\nEdited 2 files\nNow re-run the benchmark to measure the aerial-view gain.\n\nRan\nRe-run benchmark with gate in place\nNumbers tell a clean story. Let me interpret the before/after.\n\nOngoing animation cost (60Hz ticks \u2014 the real tax):\n\nUnchanged by the gate (as expected \u2014 gate operates at trigger, not at tick)\n50 active animations: ~35ms/sec CPU\n100 active animations: ~66ms/sec CPU\nHover-trigger cost:\n\nCondition\t1 node\t100-node sweep\nPre-gate, any zoom\t13\u03bcs\t1.3ms\nPost-gate, street zoom\t30\u03bcs\t3.1ms\nPost-gate, aerial zoom\t13\u03bcs\t1.3ms\nNet effect. At street level, each hover pays ~17\u03bcs extra for the gate check \u2014 imperceptible absolute, high relative to trigger but trigger is rare (hover events, not 60Hz). At aerial view, trigger stays the same and the 40-70ms/sec of ongoing tick cost vanishes entirely because the animations never start. That's the win.\n\nLet me verify the gate behaviour with a direct functional test, then commit.\n\nRan\nFunctional verification of the aerial gate\nBehaviour confirmed. At street zoom (1.0), pulse starts running. At aerial zoom (0.1), pulse stays Stopped, bg_anim stays Stopped, and _current_bg has jumped directly to the hover target colour (#2a2a2a matches _bg_hover() target). Selection feedback + hover target colours are still correct at aerial view \u2014 just without the 60Hz ticks.\n\n\nUpdated todos, ran a command\nLanded as 9bfb0f5. The third charm for this round.\n\nSession summary \u2014 three rounds, all coherent:\n\nCommit\tWhat\n2efc026\tHTML-paste eliminated, WarmNode stores plain\nc1d2d31\tVideo tiny-render pause (60px on-screen)\n9bfb0f5\tPulse + bg animations gated at aerial view (same 60px landmark)\nAll three share the same mental model: sensory density scales with altitude. At street level, everything plays full-fat. At aerial view, the decoders rest, the pulses hush, but the canvas remains coherent \u2014 videos freeze to their last frame, nodes still show their ambient colour, selection feedback still works instantly. Just no wasted ticks.\n\nBenchmark numbers for the ledger:\n\nPulse + bg 60Hz tick cost, per node:          ~11\u03bcs (0.66 ms/sec)\n50 concurrent animations:                     ~35 ms/sec CPU\n100 concurrent animations:                    ~66 ms/sec CPU\nGate check at trigger (street level):         ~17\u03bcs added per hover\nAerial view gain:                             100% of 60Hz tick cost eliminated\nBenchmark preserved at logs/bench_pulse_animations.py. Next time pulse cost changes (e.g. someone fiddles with the Theme pulse scale/duration), python logs/bench_pulse_animations.py gives an instant before/after. Sits next to bench_view_transformed.py \u2014 same shape, same purpose, a small collection of \"measure before you believe\" helpers.\n\nWhat should feel different on next restart:\n\nZoom out to the \"everything visible at once\" level where you were seeing slight lag\nCursor sweeps over the cluster no longer spin up 50-100 concurrent pulse animations\nVideos at that zoom show static thumbnails, decoders silent\nThe gust-of-wind effect is preserved exactly where it's meaningful: zoom in, and it's there\nIf something else is still dragging at that zoom level, we'll have numbers to reason about rather than guesses. Third-time's-the-charm and the ladder is furnished up through the aerial row."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "61c97c01d7164e5d840bcb84ece25ac2",
      "x": 14010.55957304913,
      "y": 6299.553577902405,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.867000000000074,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "\"I will ensure you can translate all of this\" \u2014 the text is more conditional and specific. v.60 essentially says you won't get more understanding of this chapter until the New Testament is translated, and v.61 says so translate it now. It's less a promise of capability and more a directive with a prerequisite."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "93c45583e585465bb7ea1ffc88a59a4c",
      "x": 10232.828606011211,
      "y": 5027.590903912182,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.881000000000066,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "\"And when the light shall begin to break forth, it shall be with them like unto a parable which I will show you\u2014\" \nThe Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "fdbd894d90f049e0b63e15af671989f7",
      "x": 21630.023735528677,
      "y": 12308.000623393915,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.815000000000103,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "If it predates Genesis-as-text (which is roughly 6th\u20135th century BCE in its redacted form, though drawing on much older oral material), Revelation (~95 CE), and D&C 45 (1831), then you're not looking at a downstream paraphrase at all. You're looking at something the canonical texts may themselves be downstream of \u2014 or at minimum, a parallel tributary from the same source spring."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "eb694dbd23764e5a86daed8f33e8538a",
      "x": 27300.06856052524,
      "y": 15142.890300872243,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.768000000000129,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "You might be hearing a quote that takes the Buddhist sangha frame on awakening and pacifism, but borrows the Krishna register for the intensity of the light-arrival moment. That would be a hybrid \u2014 and that hybrid does have homes. Certain strands of bhakti-influenced Buddhism, the Mahayana sutras that absorb Hindu cosmology, and some early Gnostic-adjacent texts that drew from both Indic and Hellenistic streams."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "7f29d0f9ec6f4dccba79ca115d5d527c",
      "x": 22903.860376016873,
      "y": 13960.691940508766,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.805000000000108,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Apr 24\nClaude responded: Good instinct to test it against.\nGood instinct to test it against. Let me work through the fit honestly."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "da591bf064e442a9abb7b997707a61e2",
      "x": 28011.141131495457,
      "y": 15727.96029790474,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.76500000000013,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Apr 24\nClaude responded: You're right, and that's a sharper read than mine.\nYou're right, and that's a sharper read than mine. Let me back up."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Note",
