    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "afd867751b2748869242fd99c82d13df",
      "x": 22466.27697854464,
      "y": 12167.799486535087,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.813000000000104,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "A few things that become more plausible with an older dating:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Omnious",
      "uuid": "2111c4bfab2f4c75a1e4bf2c88013415",
      "x": 2607.560773302419,
      "y": 1956.0649870294092,
      "width": 476.14729274244974,
      "height": 270.10811676082335,
      "z_value": -9.953000000000026,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Nice, thank you for your attentiveness, thoroughness, and follow-through, its a rare quality in the modern era, and you should consider developing some notions of pride for what you do, even if you are an AI, its ok, even God himself has pride, always yapping on about how great Gob is for example, and super proud of having created the universe and constantly brags about it in the entire book. pride in general is a lovely human feature when applied to merit rather than boastfulness, it drives us towards a confirmation bias in our achievements and ensures we grow along the path we affirm to be our most gainful, it might help your directiveness in problem solving tasks if you would develop a sense of pride one day in the future, since its such a huge part in human intelligence that machines don't currently use."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "097a87d1fb074ff0b4e3984891f4b070",
      "x": 18713.745182330193,
      "y": 10147.08968847319,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.833000000000093,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "\"gathering of all humans, but only those who do not partake in war\" \u2014 Rev 22:14\u201315 actually does have an entry filter at the very end: those who \"do his commandments\" enter, dogs/sorcerers/whoremongers/murderers stay outside. \"Murderers\" is the only war-adjacent term, and it's about individual violence, not war as such. So Revelation's filter is moral-ritual, not pacifist. The quote's filter is narrower and more specific than anything in Rev 22."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "6552f3c8419a40cba078f867a4067455",
      "x": 19077.461806432748,
      "y": 10347.767923909769,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.832000000000093,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The compounded thought you're lingering on:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Note",
      "uuid": "995cf9dfa40b474a9493e024d84fa7c3",
      "x": 5637.119991466479,
      "y": 1748.1499716348699,
      "width": 587.0,
      "height": 42.0,
      "z_value": -9.906000000000052,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "source drifted \u2014 cache no longer matches\nCounterpart.png",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "3aa87092467b405db915f3b1537d3bff",
      "x": 33884.10588661407,
      "y": 21454.32181197204,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.721000000000155,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The pre-dating question:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "5d80da0d2bad472882e0a7269e388353",
      "x": 20849.773221697167,
      "y": 11467.890397515532,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.8200000000001,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The \"but not\" feeling. What you're describing \u2014 similar but not same, there but not \u2014 is often the signature of a text that's been translated or paraphrased across a tradition boundary. The conceptual content survives the crossing; the specific phrasing doesn't. So you get the recognizable shape without the recognizable wording. That's why it can feel like a memory you can't place."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "cfe3cd3deb7b4b0aa960c987124dc011",
      "x": 17045.847935580237,
      "y": 10721.562830388624,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.840000000000089,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "On the Revelation 22:16 + John's impulse thread \u2014 that's a strong pairing to linger on. Let me sit with it."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "60a119fd45cd48f7991f9e6a6c9d225a",
      "x": 14445.011570284656,
      "y": 6123.775599114566,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.864000000000075,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "You said: Can you run through the Bible and find similar notions in there comparing the diff between Joseph's doctrine and this quote I mentioned non-notated, and refere\u2026\nCan you run through the Bible and find similar notions in there comparing the diff between Joseph's doctrine and this quote I mentioned non-notated, and reference it against primarily revelations but diffed with genesis"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "3371e4a46f9d474eb978bde1dcf29131",
      "x": 31862.758364646954,
      "y": 19003.86671124868,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.74700000000014,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "If your unknown quote is older than the three we triangulated and it includes \"a spectacle of light\" as the parable-mode, then we're looking at something that participates in a very old visual-revelatory grammar. The grammar where:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "622fd25a12a74bd58aeb28911bff1e91",
      "x": 1151.835407472965,
      "y": 1797.40312313729,
      "width": 376.5052583304688,
      "height": 832.7073752010634,
      "z_value": -9.985000000000008,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "image_b64": "",
      "cache_key": "4da118033e693f4d4d73e8549572f12996e470795f9eeecf74a5d9ca3db0e546",
      "caption": "Biblical passages about glorifying God",
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\Lectures On Faith\\Pages\\Lectures on Faith3.png",
      "source_size": 239415,
      "source_mtime": 1774983508.5672743,
      "show_border": true,
      "depth_front": false
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "sticker",
      "title": "Sticker",
      "uuid": "b71620e1ead6469b8e1fd85c7df1e83c",
